---
// Comic-strip widget — Clanky's packet journey across a global VPC
// 4 panels, click-to-advance
---

<div class="comic-widget" data-comic-widget>
  <div class="comic-header">
    <span class="comic-title">🎬 Clanky's packet journey</span>
    <span class="comic-meta" data-panel-counter>Panel 1 of 4</span>
  </div>

  <div class="comic-stage" data-stage>

    <div class="comic-panel" data-panel="1">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 600 240" width="100%">
        <rect x="40" y="60" width="200" height="160" rx="10" fill="#E6F1FB" stroke="#185FA5" stroke-width="0.5"/>
        <text x="140" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="500" font-size="13" fill="#0C447C">us-central1 subnet</text>
        <text x="140" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#185FA5">10.0.0.0/20</text>
        <rect x="60" y="125" width="160" height="40" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#185FA5" stroke-width="0.5"/>
        <text x="140" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#0C447C" font-weight="500">api-server-1</text>
        <text x="140" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#185FA5">10.0.0.7</text>

        <text x="350" y="100" font-size="32">🤖</text>
        <text x="395" y="115" font-size="13" font-weight="500" fill="#f0eee6">"OK, I have a packet for the EU server.</text>
        <text x="395" y="135" font-size="13" font-weight="500" fill="#f0eee6">Time to find a route!"</text>

        <line x1="220" y1="145" x2="345" y2="115" stroke="#efad4e" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="comic-caption">
        <strong>Panel 1 — origin.</strong> A request comes in to <code>api-server-1</code> in the us-central1 subnet. It needs to call <code>eu-customer-api</code> for some GDPR-relevant customer data. Clanky (our packet) gets ready to travel.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comic-panel" data-panel="2">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 600 240" width="100%">
        <rect x="20" y="20" width="560" height="200" rx="10" fill="none" stroke="#3C3489" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
        <text x="40" y="42" font-size="11" font-weight="500" fill="#3C3489">VPC: production-network (global)</text>

        <rect x="50" y="60" width="160" height="140" rx="8" fill="#E6F1FB" stroke="#185FA5" stroke-width="0.5"/>
        <text x="130" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="500" font-size="12" fill="#0C447C">us-central1</text>
        <text x="130" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#185FA5">10.0.0.0/20</text>

        <rect x="390" y="60" width="160" height="140" rx="8" fill="#E1F5EE" stroke="#0F6E56" stroke-width="0.5"/>
        <text x="470" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="500" font-size="12" fill="#085041">europe-west1</text>
        <text x="470" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#0F6E56">10.0.16.0/20</text>

        <text x="240" y="125" font-size="22">🤖</text>
        <text x="220" y="155" font-size="11" fill="#f0eee6">"Hmm, the destination IP is</text>
        <text x="220" y="170" font-size="11" fill="#f0eee6">10.0.16.42 — that's in the EU subnet."</text>

        <line x1="210" y1="130" x2="390" y2="130" stroke="#efad4e" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="comic-caption">
        <strong>Panel 2 — routing.</strong> Clanky checks the VPC's routing table. The destination IP <code>10.0.16.42</code> falls within the europe-west1 subnet's range (<code>10.0.16.0/20</code>). The VPC knows exactly where to send him. <em>No public internet involved. No VPN. No peering. They're on the same network already.</em>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comic-panel" data-panel="3">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 600 240" width="100%">
        <rect x="20" y="20" width="560" height="200" rx="10" fill="none" stroke="#3C3489" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="6 4"/>
        <text x="40" y="42" font-size="11" font-weight="500" fill="#3C3489">VPC: production-network — Google's backbone</text>

        <text x="60" y="135" font-size="12">🇺🇸</text>
        <text x="540" y="135" font-size="12">🇪🇺</text>

        <line x1="80" y1="130" x2="540" y2="130" stroke="#efad4e" stroke-width="2"/>

        <text x="200" y="120" font-size="22">🤖💨</text>

        <text x="300" y="170" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="500" fill="#efad4e">~80ms across the Atlantic</text>
        <text x="300" y="186" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#d3d1c7">Google's private fiber, encrypted in transit, never touches the public internet</text>
      </svg>
      <div class="comic-caption">
        <strong>Panel 3 — transit.</strong> Clanky travels across Google's <strong>private fiber backbone</strong> — the same physical infrastructure that powers Google Search and YouTube. Encrypted in transit by default. <em>This is genuinely how it works:</em> traffic between regions inside the same VPC stays inside Google's network the entire way.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="comic-panel" data-panel="4">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 600 240" width="100%">
        <rect x="40" y="60" width="200" height="160" rx="10" fill="#E1F5EE" stroke="#0F6E56" stroke-width="0.5"/>
        <text x="140" y="85" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="500" font-size="13" fill="#085041">europe-west1 subnet</text>
        <text x="140" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#0F6E56">10.0.16.0/20</text>
        <rect x="60" y="125" width="160" height="40" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#0F6E56" stroke-width="0.5"/>
        <text x="140" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#085041" font-weight="500">eu-customer-api</text>
        <text x="140" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#0F6E56">10.0.16.42</text>

        <text x="295" y="100" font-size="32">🤖</text>
        <text x="345" y="115" font-size="13" font-weight="500" fill="#f0eee6">"Made it! Delivered the request.</text>
        <text x="345" y="135" font-size="13" font-weight="500" fill="#f0eee6">Now I'll fly back with the response."</text>
        <text x="345" y="160" font-size="11" fill="#d3d1c7">Total round trip: ~160ms</text>

        <line x1="240" y1="145" x2="290" y2="115" stroke="#efad4e" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 3"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="comic-caption">
        <strong>Panel 4 — delivery.</strong> Clanky arrives at <code>eu-customer-api</code> on its private IP. The whole journey took ~80ms one-way over Google's backbone. The application code on both sides has no idea this packet just crossed the Atlantic — the VPC made it look like the two VMs were neighbors. <em>That's what "global VPC" actually means in practice.</em>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="comic-controls">
    <button data-comic-prev disabled>← Previous</button>
    <div class="comic-dots" data-comic-dots>
      <span class="comic-dot active" data-dot="1"></span>
      <span class="comic-dot" data-dot="2"></span>
      <span class="comic-dot" data-dot="3"></span>
      <span class="comic-dot" data-dot="4"></span>
    </div>
    <button data-comic-next>Next →</button>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLDivElement>('[data-comic-widget]').forEach((root) => {
    const stage = root.querySelector<HTMLDivElement>('[data-stage]')!;
    const counter = root.querySelector<HTMLSpanElement>('[data-panel-counter]')!;
    const prev = root.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-comic-prev]')!;
    const next = root.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-comic-next]')!;
    const dots = root.querySelectorAll<HTMLSpanElement>('.comic-dot');
    const panels = root.querySelectorAll<HTMLDivElement>('.comic-panel');
    const total = panels.length;
    let current = 1;

    function show(n: number) {
      panels.forEach((p, i) => {
        p.classList.toggle('active', i === n - 1);
      });
      dots.forEach((d, i) => {
        d.classList.toggle('active', i === n - 1);
      });
      counter.textContent = `Panel ${n} of ${total}`;
      prev.disabled = n === 1;
      next.disabled = n === total;
      next.textContent = n === total ? '✓ End' : 'Next →';
    }

    prev.addEventListener('click', () => { if (current > 1) { current--; show(current); } });
    next.addEventListener('click', () => { if (current < total) { current++; show(current); } });
    dots.forEach((d, i) => {
      d.addEventListener('click', () => { current = i + 1; show(current); });
    });

    show(1);
  });
</script>

<style is:global>
  .comic-widget {
    margin: 2rem 0;
    background: #2c2a26;
    border: 1px solid #4a4a48;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .comic-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #4a4a48;
  }
  .comic-title {
    color: #efad4e;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .comic-meta {
    color: #b4b2a9;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .comic-stage {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 380px;
  }
  .comic-panel {
    display: none;
    animation: fadeIn 0.3s ease-in;
  }
  .comic-panel.active {
    display: block;
  }
  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(4px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  .comic-caption {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: #1a1815;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    color: #f0eee6;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .comic-caption strong {
    color: #efad4e;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .comic-caption em { color: #d3d1c7; font-style: italic; }
  .comic-caption code {
    background: #2c2a26;
    color: #efad4e;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
  .comic-controls {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .comic-controls button {
    background: transparent;
    color: #f0eee6;
    border: 1px solid #4a4a48;
    padding: 8px 14px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-size: 13px;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .comic-controls button:hover:not(:disabled) {
    background: #1a1815;
    border-color: #efad4e;
  }
  .comic-controls button:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: default;
  }
  .comic-dots {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .comic-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #4a4a48;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .comic-dot.active {
    background: #efad4e;
  }
  .comic-dot:hover {
    background: #b4b2a9;
  }
</style>
